: This species is currently known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54B5880EFFD7E524534D80C2609CF856" box="[872,919,1994,2018]" pageId="22" pageNumber="139">type</typeStatus>
locality in South 
<collectingCountry id="F319763CFFD7E524547280C1679BF855" box="[1111,1168,1993,2017]" name="India" pageId="22" pageNumber="139">India</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFD7E52454BB80C167ECF855" box="[1182,1255,1993,2017]" captionStart="Map 7" captionStartId="67.[151,196,1246,1267]" captionTargetBox="[351,1198,232,1238]" captionTargetId="figure-79@67.[351,1198,232,1238]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Map 7: Revised distributions of Zyras gardneri (black circles), Z. hirsutiventris (white diamonds), Z. parageminus (black triangles), Z. hastatus (white triangle), Z. hirtus (white circles), and Z. latilobatus (star) in India and adjacent regions." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742413/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="139">Map 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
